snippet: Two car bombings in the Baghdad area killed more than 30 Shiite pilgrims at the end of the celebration.
abstract: Security clampdown aimed at protecting Shiite pilgrims fails to prevent a new round of carnage as two car bombings in Baghdad kill more than 30 at the end of a weeklong celebration; attacks represent an embarrassment to the Iraqi army and police, and raise questions about the ability of Iraq’s security forces to protect the population.

byline.original: By DURAID ADNAN and TIM ARANGO

lead_paragraph: Two car bombings in the Baghdad area killed more than 30 Shiite pilgrims at the end of the celebration.

headline.seo: Shiite Pilgrims Targeted in Car Bombings
headline.main: 2 Car Bombs Target Shiites in Baghdad
headline.print_headline: 2 Car Bombs Target Shiites In Baghdad
